<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1061" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1061">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-02-17"><hi rend="italic">February 17,
                                    1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I am
                            commanded by the Queen to convey to the President the expression of Her
                            Majesty’s sympathy with the American people on the occasion of the sad
                            disaster which has befallen their Navy by the loss of the battle ship
                                <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi> and of so many members of her crew. I
                            request that you will be good enough to transmit the above message to
                            its high destination.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>